transfer_from_account -> string, trim, keep as text
transfer_to_account   -> string, trim, keep as text
transfer_amount       -> number/currency, "$1,200.50" -> "1200.50"
transfer_date         -> date, normalize to YYYY-MM-DD, within 365 days
loan_type             -> constrained allowed value
vehicle_make          -> string
vehicle_model         -> string
vehicle_year          -> number, 4 digits, > 1990
card_type             -> constrained: ATM or Debit
zip_code              -> string, exactly 5 digits, keep leading zero


missing entity -> skip
null value -> skip
extra entity not in schema -> ignore
invalid value -> remove entity and entity_was_explicit
valid value -> keep normalized value and entity_was_explicit


string:
- trim spaces
- keep value as text

number:
- remove currency symbols/commas when rule is currency
- validate numeric format
- keep as string in final map

date:
- resolve natural language date to YYYY-MM-DD
- reject past dates
- reject dates beyond 365 days

CONSTRAINED:
- value must match allowed values
- compare case-insensitively
- output canonical allowed value

zip_code:
- treat as string
- exactly 5 digits
- keep leading zeros

vehicle_year:
- numeric
- four digits


Test Coverage

Validation should be covered by tests for:

- valid date resolution
- rejected date removal
- currency normalization
- ZIP code leading zero preservation
- constrained value matching
- invalid constrained values
- vehicle year validation
- ignored extra Bedrock entities
- skipped missing/null values


## Entity Rules

| Entity | Type | Data Type | Validation / Normalization |
|---|---|---|---|
| transfer_from_account | OPEN | string | Trim and keep as text |
| transfer_to_account | OPEN | string | Trim and keep as text |
| transfer_amount | OPEN | number | Currency allowed. `$1,200.50` becomes `1200.50` |
| transfer_date | OPEN | date | Resolve to `YYYY-MM-DD`; must be within 365 days |
| loan_type | CONSTRAINED | string | Must match allowed loan type |
| vehicle_make | OPEN | string | Trim and keep as text |
| vehicle_model | OPEN | string | Trim and keep as text |
| vehicle_year | OPEN | number | Must be 4 digits and greater than 1990 |
| card_type | CONSTRAINED | string | Must be `ATM` or `Debit` |
| zip_code | CONSTRAINED | string | Must be exactly 5 digits; keep leading zeros |

General Rules

- Only entities defined in the schema are accepted.
- Extra entities returned by Bedrock are ignored.
- Missing entities are skipped.
- Null or empty values are skipped.
- Invalid values are removed.
- If an entity is removed, its `_was_explicit` flag is also removed.
- Valid values are normalized based on data type.

currency:
- belongs to number validation
- "$1,200.50" -> "1200.50"
